{"cursor":"13798","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Mount Hermon other_name='Arabic:' Jabal ash-Shaykh 'Hebrew:' Har\n| Hermon photo = Hermonsnow.jpg photo_caption = Mount Hermon, viewed from\n| Mount Bental in the Golan Heights photo_size = 250 elevation_m = 2814\n| elevation_ref = prominence_m = 1804 prominence_ref = map = Golan Heights\n| map_caption = Mount Hermon's summit straddles the border between Lebanon and\n| Syria. label_position = right listing = Country high point Ultra\n| location= Syria (southern slopes are located in the Israeli-occupied\n| Golan Heights) Lebanon range = Anti-Lebanon mountain range lat_d\n| = 33 | lat_m = 24 | lat_s = 58 | lat_NS = N long_d = 35 | long_m = 51 | long_s\n| = 27 | long_EW = E coordinates_ref = topo = type = age = first_ascent =\n| easiest_route =\n}}\n\n'Mount Hermon' ( / ALA-LC: Jabal al-Shaykh / \"Mountain of the Chief\" \"Jabal\nHaramun\"; , Har Hermon, \"Mount Hermon\") is a mountain cluster in the Anti-\nLebanon mountain range. Its summit straddles the border between Syria and Leban-\non [http://mapper.acme.com/?ll=33.416111,35.8575&z=14&t=R&marker0=33.416111-\n,35.8575,Mount%20Hermon ACME Mapper terrain display] and, at 2,814 m\n(9,232 ft) above sea level, is the highest point in Syria. On\nthe top there is âHermon Hotelâ, in the buffer zone between Syria and Israeli-\noccupied territory, the highest permanent manned UN position in the world. The southern slopes of Mount Hermon extend to the\nIsraeli-occupied portion of the Golan Heights, where the Mount Hermon ski resort\nis located. [http://www.popularmechanics.com/outdoors/sports/skiing-\nboarding/the-worlds-18-strangest-ski-resorts-2#fbIndex2 The World's 18 Strangest\nSki Resorts: The Mount Hermon Ski Resort], Shannon Hassett, Popular\nMechanics A peak in this area rising to 2,236 m (7,336 ft) is\nthe highest elevation in Israeli-controlled territory.\n","linknr":331,"url":"Mount_Hermon","recorded":1374760